                    <span>While Computer Security Basics is slightly outdated, it nonetheless provides a good introduction to computer security.<P>It gives a great overview of the DoD Orange Book, but the Orange Book is now obsolete and is replaced by the Common Criteria.<P>Hopefully, the authors Russell & Gangemi are worlking on an update, as they are excellent writers.</span>
                  
